\title{Concert: To the Soul's Quiet Harbour}
\tag{cmc}
\author{liamoc}
\p{This is a special edition of [[loc-000P]] where I share the programme for the second church choir concert of 2026, \em{To the Soul's Quiet Harbour}, continuing in the funerial theme established by our [first concert](loc-003R). The student musicians from Burgmann Anglican School joined us at [All Saints Ainslie](https://allsaintsainslie.org.au) to perform an afternoon of chamber music to a fairly full house. We sang pretty well despite being lopsided in numbers (I was the only tenor.)}
\p{The main works performed by the choir (interspersed by instrumental performances from Burgmann) were the first four of Parry's \em{Songs of Farewell}: [My soul, there is a country](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F9AacmOZp3g), then [I know my soul hath power](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o9tsW2Kgdts), then [Never weatherbeaten sail](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F5fpVWHeCxk) and [There is an old belief](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XNmwIiq0ESY). The last item of the concert was [O How Amiable](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Yr9O440q998) by Ralph Vaughan Williams, which we sung with pipe organ, choir, \em{and} instruments. }
\p{I think the concert went rather well. Thanks to all who put the effort in to make it possible, and to everyone that attended!}
